[Although ProMED-mail does not cover pertussis regularly, regular outbreaks
of the disease have continued to occur in the USA and elsewhere despite
aggressive universal childhood immunization programs. The development of a
pertussis vaccine consisting of pertussis toxoids as opposed to the older
vaccine -- which was a killed, whole-cell product -- has improved tolerance
but not immunogenicity. This product, DTaP, has been used in the pediatric
vaccination sequence for some time. As noted above, the Tdap variation is
now approved in adolescents and contains lower amounts of both diphtheria
and pertussis components than the pediatric vaccine. Vaccination in
adolescence should prolong immunity, but an additional booster will
probably be needed later in life. - Mod.LL]
